{"id":227449,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ilan_Ramon","text":"Colonel Ilan Ramon (, born Ilan Wolferman; June 20, 1954 - February 1, 2003) was an Israeli air force pilot and the only Israeli astronaut, and a national hero. He was a member of STS-107 mission crew and he died during Space Shuttle Columbia disaster in 2003.\nHis mother was a holocaust survivor (at Auschwitz concentration camp) and his father fought for Israeli independence. Ramon was married to activist Rona Ramon.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Colonel","surface_form":"Colonel","offset":0},{"uri":"June_20","surface_form":"June 20","offset":43},{"uri":"1954","surface_form":"1954","offset":52},{"uri":"February_1","surface_form":"February 1","offset":59},{"uri":"2003","surface_form":"2003","offset":71},{"uri":"Israel","surface_form":"Israel","offset":84},{"uri":"Israeli_Air_Force","surface_form":"air force","offset":92},{"uri":"Pilot","surface_form":"pilot","offset":102},{"uri":"Astronaut","surface_form":"astronaut","offset":129},{"uri":"STS-107","surface_form":"STS-107","offset":180},{"uri":"Space_Shuttle_Columbia","surface_form":"Space Shuttle Columbia","offset":220},{"uri":"Holocaust","surface_form":"holocaust","offset":278},{"uri":"Auschwitz_concentration_camp","surface_form":"Auschwitz concentration camp","offset":301},{"uri":"1948_Arab%E2%80%93Israeli_War","surface_form":"Israeli independence","offset":357},{"uri":"Rona_Ramon","surface_form":"Rona Ramon","offset":409}]}